<br />

<br />
On this one I'd like to add that they already have this in game.  Well at least a portion of it.  For those of you who remember hunting Stonebrunt Mountains might remember the kitty city.  The one thing you could NOT do was run in there wiht an illusion.  ANY illusion.  So is SOE had that kind of issue with some faction problem they could have easily dropped in a few well placed mobs that agro'd on illusions.  Top em off with See invis and BINGO problem solved.
<br />

<br />
Since SOE decided to completely BORK the entire Illusion line including the one REQUIRED to get certain mana spells by ourselves yet left other classes alone says volumes for what SOE thought about our class.  Of course they may not have been aware that that was something they could do, or maybe see invis and see illusion don't stack. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
My idea as a top ten list item then?
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Bring back illusion faction</span>
<br />

<br />
I would LOVE to get Illusions back, because using them as faction adjuster was a big part of the class.  Being able to wander the hole since you could pop on Earth Elemental, or werewolf/boon for getting better bloodsaber,  was a way to use the abilities of the class for epic work.  Like charm is. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
I think Lilly's idea has some merit, but needs a LOT of work.  The racial thing is not the way to go (IMO).  Factions should be brought back though.  It makes no sense to see Werewolf/Boon people sitting in the city whiling away the hours at a loom. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />  Although I like illusions, I don't think they should be used to address all the shortcomings we have been handed recently.
<br />

<br />
Unfortunate for me I have no better ideas right now. <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="icon_sad.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
