<span class="postbody">Phylassein asked me:
<br />
"
<br />
-------are you old school, if so you know you can go with puller anytime he goes out => cast sight or its lower counterpart 
<br />
-------we had communication that folks from the old world don't seem to acknowledge anymore, the puller, the melee, the healer and the enchanter always knew what we each could deal with and planned it................of course this meant playing regularly within a circle of folks you could call friend in game. "
<br />

<br />
Yes, quite old. However, in the old days, no ench went with the puller.  In guk, the ench and everyone else stayed in camp, you wait there and then when the puller had 6 mobs, you just area mezed them.  Ahhh..the good old days of area mez... This continued up through sol b, Karnors Castle and into sebilis.  Once luclin came out it was critical in aoe groups to stay in camp and be ready for chain stuning. Still we had little reason for geting out of camp or knowing what mobs were incoming. We stunned them all.  Casting Cast sight was usefull to check on the progress of the puller in Acrylia Caverns, and after that was nerfed, in the Deep and Fungus grove.  The disadvantage is the loss of stamina as you presumeably stop breathing. But even there, no reason ever to leave camp. So historically, in the "old World" of which you speak,  ench's NEVER had reason to travel with the puller or otherwise coordinate with them. 
<br />

<br />
This changed in the new would of POP with Plane of valor, there was again room enough to travel and plan when mobs needed to be pacified in conjunction with the puller.  In Bastion of thunder, we would be moving around to mez or charm mobs, and this was involving and fun. In LDON, moving was forced and pulls would often have adds, coordination was usefull, but with a monk or bard pulling, not really required. 
<br />
  
<br />
In GOD, we had to move and most especially charm.  That was the biggest thing and the only reason I was invited for groups there. I had to charm pets for killing the named for getting the KT flag.  It was an over reliance on one spell, and it was very stressful, since a moment of inattention when charm breaks would lead to wipes with long cr. 
<br />

<br />
Now I don't have to charm, it is a lot less stressful, but I am unable to mez many times and resists suck, death is quick.  There are no options anymore, I can't stun if I get a resist, I can't do anything except hope my instant aa rune will be up and keep me alive for 6 seconds to re-cast my mez. We have lost alot of power in GOD. However, DON seems to have a better balance, mobs are not overly resistant, they have wanderers that need to be mezed and hidden mobs that add on a pull. I find myself a bit more needed again.  Now, if only we had some meaningful illusions... <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />

<br />
