<br />

<br />
Keeping an eye out depends on the place you are in. If you are in a camp type enviornment with enough space, for example an open zone like Overthere, Dreadlands or KT, then you can use the view feature to look back down at the camp from way in front of you and see and target any mobs that add. If you are in a maze camp, it is more difficult to get a good view and you need to look forward.  However, seeing the mobs is not the problem, it is that they resist and you die. With leader aa's it is easy to see which mob the tank is attackign and which to try to mez. 
<br />

<br />
And I have never left a group if somone has a suggestion for me in terms of what needs to be done, that would sort of contradict the idea of "we had communication that folks from the old world don't seem to acknowledge anymore" that you speak so highly about above.  How can there be any communication if you won't listen when people offer suggestions and you leave the group when they try?  Hmmm.. ? <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
