Don't confuse role-play with EQ.  EQ is only marginally RP, even I gave up trying to do that a long time ago.  It was in teh way in pick up groups who rarely liked any decent RP, and with my RL friends we wanted to get done so RP was tossed there more often than not.  Faction may/may not decay over time, but decrying it not decaying only means you would rather have a different system.  I would prefer a better system that had permanent changes to your max faction.  You have a current faction, and a max faction.  You can increase your faction, but the lower it gets the lower your MAX faction would be able to get.  That would mean no ping pong like the Velious faction were done.  Cap your Dragon and Thug faction for this week cause we are dropping Tormax and you want to quest the head if you get it.  Whoops, not enough DKP/luck on random.  No worries . . . Tomorrow get the faction back up since you raided Thurg and got Dain's head so you can finish that quets before next weeks raid on the dragons, which will get your faction back up for that next Tormax drop.
<br />

<br />
When you make 9 of your top 10 relating to illusions, then yes you are attemping to make illusions the be all end all of the class.  That's just my opinion, but it seems to have merit.  Not all of them are bad, I liked some, but I don;t think making a new root via illusion is good, nor is mana regen via illusion.  We get minimal abilities form illusions, and that is nice, but I don't think extending the abilities on illusions helps, I think factions and or the ability to hide them is good.
<br />

<br />
Now if you want an illusion that can mask our religious faction, I can see that.  An illusion that is not projectable but makes us non KoS to scout some portion of a zone?  I want it.
<br />

<br />
Illusions to cause fear?  Nope, we have that in . . . Fear spells.
<br />

<br />
Illusions to cause damage?  Nope we have that in . . . Dots and Nukes.
<br />

<br />
Illusions to root?  Nope we already have . . . Root.
<br />

<br />
I can relate to the idea that an Enc is powerful in illusions and that is why you work them all towards that end.  But I don't think we should head that way.  Lessen the insane MR on mobs and flag them immune to certain spells.
<br />

<br />
Things I'd like changed:
<br />

<br />
Less of a raid only oriented game.  I want some raids, I just don't want the entire end game to be only that.  DoN seems to be a big step in the right direction from all accounts, and once I buy it I can say for certain. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />  Tradeskilling should NOT require being in the top end raid guild.
<br />

<br />
Factions brought back on illusions.  And add some interesting illusions at the same time.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />  Say the religion faction mask, or maybe an illusion that has a particular religion (improved DE that also has Inny religion).
<br />

<br />
PoP should have been a quest dream, what with each player having the diety available.  If you are going to RP, make sure that improving YOUR diey faction becomes imprtant.  If they added quests to the old PoP zones you could also add in a quest to change religion, that way your DE can actually make friends with felwithe.  Make it involved, make it fun, make it a quest kinda like the epic. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Change EQ back to EverQUEST, instead of Everloot. Real engaging quests and not farm mob y loot item x get item z.  The Qeynos badge quests are a great example of what could be tried, Coldain rings and Shawl of olden times are even better examples.
<br />

<br />
Add challenging single group/solo missions for the appropriate level that CAN be completed solo.  Don't make them time sinks, maybe make them instanced, force characters to use the SKILLS, not the hours. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Fix the charm nerf debacle.  I never charmed much, my only real success was once in blackburrow at level 12.  I charmed a tough one and was able to take him into the heart of the dubgeon with a group and we got into a furball, but we made it.  Challenge! Tough! Almost dead! It was FUN!!! <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />  Have tried to work on charm skills, but once you get to a certain level it's ont quite as fun to die over and over, just so you get your timing down.  I respect teh ones who did it.  Actually I admire them, but with the nerf in place I see no reason to practice skills that will be useless.  Except for the Pooka trial.  Since I will most likely be along with a group I should have a snare person along, and hopefully a shammy.  Or I can take the long approach should I ever desire to a) purchase said expansion. . . and b) get the flag.
<br />

<br />
Failing the charm nerf fix, then give us at least a REASONABLE pet.  Make it come through AA's (possible high cost and lvl reqs), but make sure we have a CHANCE to play in some places.  My brand new 62 pet does okay in the Hole, and in PoN, as long as I don't let it tank.  So how in the world is he supposed to be able to tank for me in higher zones since I have to move out of the quickly becoming green zones I inhabit now?  Sure he's low DPS that's fine, but his mitigation and HP are awful.  If he takes a LONG time to drop mobs, well that's the price I pay for being an ENC.  But a MUCH improved Shiny BoB as far as survivable would not be game breaking.
<br />

<br />
Remove the Peridot cost on runes.  If clerics have no cost on components then we should not have it either.  The rune is fairly useless as it is, even in the few places we CAN use it, it's really not enough.  When fighting in PoN on lt blue trash, I usually have to re-rune at least once, and that's with constant refresh of berserk, and having the shammy load up on dots AND meleeing.  The only one with out a dot cost is arcane, which is what I use now since I don't have the inclination to load up packs with dots.
<br />

<br />
Well, well.  Maybe I have some thoughts on what I'd like to see fixed after all. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
