Part of this is because they don't have a WILLPOWER stat.  In old pnp we used willpower to check against a myriad of things that attempted to take over control of the characters mind.  Since most of our spells seem to indicate that we affect the mind directly, this would be where the resist should be.  Doesn't exist in EQ though.  That would give us the out we would need to move some of the spells they didn't like to the new resist, while allowing our direct spells to still take effect.
