<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Unmei wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
I'm a big fan of the "varied mez" ideas. This absurd "one size fits all" mez spell stuff is for the birds. We should have: 
<br />

<br />
A) Fewer identical mez spells. Give us a "basic" mez at our first level of each expansion (like apathy in PoP) and a "high end" mez towards the end of our progression in each expansion (like bliss in PoP). Heck, Ideally, we would get -one- "generic" mez each expansion - a high end one like Euphoria. Felicity shouldn't exist at all, and Bliss should go to 70. 
<br />

<br />
B) A "lockdown" mez. 100% more mana than the equivalent "generic" mez. 2.0 second cast time. -40 resist mod. 4 tick duration. Possibly a short recast (4 seconds?) to keep it from being the only mezz used during lockdown. 
<br />

<br />
C) A "holddown" mez. 50% more mana than the equivalent "generic" mez. 8 second cast time. No resist mod. 20 tick duration. 
<br />

<br />
D) A PBAoE mez. 1.5 second casting time. Just like WoM only maybe give it a -10 resist mod. This should be in addition to a stun (which should also cast in 1.0 or 1.5 seconds, dangit. 2 seconds is stupid for a PB defense spell.)</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
On the head.  I liked being able to save groups with being able to multitask slow/mez and figuring out what to use where.  I never charm as I see it as driving a wedge between an enchanter and a group, which I've always enjoyedmore. If they want to make it group friendly woopie, but I've never really cared one way or the other.  When I do usually use it, its on mez immune mobs, ghetto mezzing.  Aside from this and fixing our 1.5's effect....
<br />

<br />
WHERE THE HELL IS A NEW FRIGGIN SLOW?~?~~??
<br />

<br />
We're the kings of haste and enchantment.  we make enchant arms to make them move faster and learn how to do that better with nearly every expansion, why the HELL can't we learn a better slow since kunark?  I have no problem having a less supierior slow then shammies, but an UPDATE for crying out loud! Beastlords have nothing about them at all that should let them slow aside from being animal shammies, and they're slowing faster than us, and only 5% less effective at it!  hell, rip the slow effect off the Serpent of Vindification and stick a new name at it and I'd at least feel better.   Our slow is kunark era and now 13 levels lower than I am.  
<br />

<br />
Fix that.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
