<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="name"><a name="99368"></a></span><span class="postdetails">#71:&nbsp;<font color=black><b></b> Author:&nbsp;<b>Stephen51</b>,&nbsp;</font></span><span class="postdetails"><font color=black></font></span>
<a href="viewtopic.php?p=99368#99368"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Posted: Thu Mar 17, 2005 10:11 am</font><span class="gen"><br>
</td></tr>
<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">It seems to me before we get to specifics on what Chanters need we need to look at the issues the Average Chanter has. These could be;
<br />
1. Use in Group Passive, (Buffs etc).
<br />
2. Use in Group Aggressive (Debuffs, Mez, Charm, CC, Nuke)
<br />
3. Survivability in groups
<br />
4. Survivability Solo
<br />

<br />
1. I dont think Chanters want much more in the Passive line. Sure if some one said, want a Self only Mana buff? Some would say yes please. But maybe they would also want a 6k Nuke, ability to feign death and so the tipping of any balance goes. Some sort of a mana refresh for the group may be good, but it would depend on what was added elsewhere. Somehow I think the average Chanter would like to see a bit more action, a bit less buffage.
<br />
2. Use in Group Agreesive. Ah the Crux I think. I dont want pets to change. I feel a bit indignant that SoE made the problem, when players took the initiative and the risk ( I am angry at the statement that charming a snorting,slobbering,procing, death machine comes with 'minimal risk' is utter nonsense. However, if we have to loose pet dps, we need something in return. Having the mob loose haste etc when charm expires is not enough. You loose the dps, what can we get in return. A possible answer is a caster pet. Just an idea, but a pet that stuns, or memblurs, or nukes. Make it so the charmed pet can be given a stun/hate proc and he becomes part of CC. Give it Nukes proc and it becomes part of the DPS. Also give the Chanter more flexibilty on commands. It just doesnt sit well that, as the masters of controlling others, we dont get basic commands such as Sit, stay, fetch until late 50's early 60's. Allow the pet to guard not just the Chanter, but other casters. This idea could be adopted for their own pets, but they would need better ac/hps. 
<br />
3. Survivability in Groups. With the higher end content comes higher end damage and the enchanters protection ramps up with that. Right? Wrong. The Self only rune should be ramped up in hps, and/or a chance to memblur proc when hit.
<br />
4. Survivability Solo. SOE says its going to improve those classes that arent able to solo well. I think the Enchanter class could do with a tweak.
<br />
An idea as above if you could summon a healing pet. (Pally pet? Cleric pet?) That could buff and heal itsself?
<br />
I think the nukes could be ramped up a little, not as high as a Mage but a little higher at least.
<br />
Possibly take away summon from non boss/raid mobs, may help us solo too.
<br />

<br />
Just a few ideas.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
