<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="name"><a name="99546"></a></span><span class="postdetails">#72:&nbsp;<font color=black><b></b> Author:&nbsp;<b>Lillywhite</b>,&nbsp;</font></span><span class="postdetails"><font color=black></font></span>
<a href="viewtopic.php?p=99546#99546"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Posted: Mon Mar 21, 2005 6:26 am</font><span class="gen"><br>
</td></tr>
<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Yakk wrote"   'Unmei wrote: 
<br />
I challenge you to create a stun that will keep us alive in today's content the way our old stuns did, without re-enabling AoE groups (which Sony has taken great pains to avoid.)  '
<br />

<br />
1.0 casting time stun. 8.0 duration. Places an "immune to stun" (or even "immune to PBAOE stun") counter on the mob that lasts 12 seconds. Zero recast delay. 
<br />

<br />
This is a PBAOE stun that will keep you alive, but will not allow AOE groups. If it gets resisted, you can simply recast it. "
<br />

<br />
Just the 1.0 casting time stun with 8 second duration and norrmal recast would be sufficient. There would be no need place an immune to future stun on it.   AOE groups would still be impossible in OOW, due to the high resist rate, summoning mobs, and intant death and wipe that would follow from a single resist on any AOE attempt.  Recall the pulling in Acrylia Caverns(AC) or fungus grove(FG) or The Deep(TD). The puller was runing with 20-30 mobs behind him.  Often they would be damaged when they got into camp and needed cleric heals right away.  The aoe groups succeeded then because the tank would live to get to camp.  
<br />

<br />
Imagine now, a hypothetical AOE group in odi/bh in mpg.  The puller invises and runs to taskfiend camp.  Then he clicks it off and begins running back.  He gets a couple mobs, one begins summoning him, he can't get away, and splat in 1 sec or less.  Imagine he does somehow get to camp with 20 mobs.  Say you have 2 enchs with the single 1 sec spell with a normal 2 second rescast.   As you recall, for AOE in luclin, we had 4 spells that you could mem and cycle through.  This provided adequate coverage and overlap.  But how many resisted? Hardly any ever did, and when they did, the timer from the last stun was still up and they were stunned the next cycle.  There were times, that some mobs did get free, cleric heals kept the ench alive long enough to recover sometimes, or other times, it was a wipe.  Imagine the situation in odi/bh.  Assume a 20% resist rate. The puller brings 20 mobs to camp, your first stun mezes all of them for 8 seconds except for 4 of them who resist.  The second ench's stun mezes 3, and leaving 1 on you.  You die in the 2 seconds it takes to recast. Group wipes.
<br />

<br />
Assume somehow that you make it past the first round.  Now the nukers need to start nuking.  Recall how many hit points the mobs have, this will take a while.  All that time, you have to surmount a 20% resist rate on 2 mobs with 2 ench's haveing just 1 stun spell.  It will be a wipe.  Imagine doing FG or TD or AC with just one 8 second stun spell for each ench where the resist rate was maybe only 5%.  It would have still been a wipe. 
<br />

<br />
A single fast 1.0 cast time normal stun spell is all we need.  AOE groups will not be possible.
<br />

<br />
Lillywhite</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
